*********************************************************************Google Cloud Essential Skills: Challenge Lab**********************************************************

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Task 1 : Create a Compute Engine instance, add necessary firewall rules.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Create a Linux VM Instance

Create a Linux virtual machine Instance , 
Name: as mentioned on the lab instruction page
Region: as mentioned on the lab instruction page

Click on Checkbox Of Allow HTTP Traffic

Click on create

Enable Public Access to VM Instance

In cloud shell Paste the Below commands


gcloud compute firewall-rules create allow-http --target-tags http-server --source-ranges 0.0.0.0/0 --allow tcp:80

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Task 2 : Configure Apache2 Web Server in your instance

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Use these commands in SSH :


sudo apt-get update

 
sudo apt-get install apache2 -y

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Task 3 : Test your server

---------------------------------------------------------------------

Click On External IP of the VM instance or this task is automatically done.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                                         

